# Sprint 06: Copy Styles and Display Parity with taskboard-supabase
# S06.ptl

**Goal:** Copy UI styles and glass-effect system from taskboard-supabase into totem-view, and replicate the three-level display structure: boards list, single board view, and task view. Achieve visual and structural parity with the reference.

**Invariants:**
- `instances/totem-view/S05-INVARIANTS.md` — glass tokens, shadow tokens, Safari backdrop-filter, modal/overlay pattern, glass buttons and cards. All new UI must comply.

**Source of truth (taskboard-supabase):**
- Display: `client/src/components/pages/Boards.vue` (boards list), `Tasks.vue` (board + task detail), `router/index.ts` (routes `/boards`, `/board/:id`).
- Components: `common/boards/BoardCard.vue`, `modules/tasksBoard/TasksBoard.vue`, `modules/tasksBoard/parts/TasksColumn.vue`, `common/tasks/TaskCard.vue`, `modules/taskDetails/TaskDetails.vue`, `wrappers/PageLayout.vue`.
- Styles: `client/src/style.css` (glass utilities, card classes), `totem/docs/UI_GLASS_EFFECT_SUMMARY.md`.

**Gate:** OPEN

## Track 1: Style and glass parity
- task: S06-T1-StyleAndGlassParity.pd

## Track 2: Display structure (boards → board → task)
- task: S06-T2-BoardsListDisplay.pd
- task: S06-T3-BoardViewDisplay.pd
- task: S06-T4-TaskDetailDisplay.pd

---

**Result (sprint outcome):** totem-view has the same three-level display (boards list, board view with columns, task detail view) and the same UI/glass styling as taskboard-supabase, in line with S05-INVARIANTS.

**Invariants for next sprints:** `instances/totem-view/S06-INVARIANTS.md` — display parity, shared UI layer, planning note (do not scope tasks narrowly).
